news.title: Noida: No zoning regulations in YEIDA master plan
news.para: Given the immense scope of industrial development in the region owing to the upcoming Noida International Airport in Jewar and mega projects like Film City, Medical Device Park and Data Park, officials said, the Authority plans to keep its sectors for development "as and when required".

news.title: Maintenance against property must be written in gift deed: Supreme Court
news.para: A bench of Justices Sanjay K Kaul and A S Oka gave this practical advice on Tuesday to senior citizens, who generally gift self-earned properties to their children in the understanding, hope and expectation that they would be well looked after in their sunset years when ailments routinely affect them.

news.title: SC quashes attachment of VGN Projects Estates' 10.6-acre land by ED under PMLA
news.para: The attachment order was passed on the basis of an allegation that the property was sold less than the guideline value of ₹387 crore causing a loss of ₹115 crore to HTL, a government of India undertaking.

news.title: Gururgam: Greenopolis buyers protest as flats not ready even after 11 years
news.para: During a protest at the Gurgaon office of the Haryana Real Estate Regulatory Authority (H-Rera) on Wednesday, the homebuyers alleged that one of the two developers - Orris Infrastructure - has utilised all money collected from them but "the project is still incomplete".

news.title: Order granting bail to DHFL's promoters not to be given effect to till Feb 1: Delhi HC
news.para: The Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) has challenged the trial court's order granting statutory bail to Wadhawan brothers because of "incomplete charge sheet".

news.title: SC extends interim bail granted to ex-CMD of Amrapali Group by 12 weeks
news.para: The top court said it will take up the application of court receiver Attorney General R Venkataramani on the floor area ration (FAR) issue on a priority basis as it concerns generation of funds for the stalled project of Amrapali.

news.title: China's Bank of Communications agrees to support eight property firms
news.para: The bank said it would deepen co-operation with the property firms, including Longfor, Gemdale and Greentown, in terms of property development loans, loans for M&A deals and bond investments, according to a statement released by the lender.

news.title: China's property sector support fails to lure bond investors
news.para: High-yield dollar-denominated bonds of companies such as Powerlong Real Estate Holdings and Country Garden Holdings have rallied since late November, cheered by the Chinese central bank's and banking regulator's 16 steps to support the ailing sector.

news.title: Blackstone CEO says financially distressed investors driving REIT redemptions
news.para: Blackstone shares have lost 15% of their value since Dec. 1, when the New York-based firm disclosed it had for the first time limited redemptions from the REIT, which is marketed to high net-worth investors rather than institutional clients like pension funds and insurance firms.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM inaugurates 4,644 flats in eight districts
news.para: Work orders under the beneficiary-led construction scheme worth 237.3 crore were issued to 11,300 beneficiaries at the rate of 2.10 lakh each. Sale deeds for plots and tenements were issued to 350 beneficiaries.

news.title: ADB approves $ 780 million loan for bettering Chennai metro rail system
news.para: “This project will expand Chennai’s metro rail system to provide a safe and integrated transport solution essential in improving urban mobility and make the city more livable,” said ADB Senior Transport Specialist for South Asia, Andri Heriawan.

news.title: Jaipur development body razes illegal resort, farmhouse
news.para: Chief controller of enforcement of JDA Raghuveer Saini said in Rajarampura village near Tatiyawas Toll Plaza on Sikar Road, a resort was constructed on about 5 bighas of a private farmland without permission and approval of JDA.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body razes three illegal buildings in Model Town Extension
news.para: The owners had failed to get the building plans approved from the civic body and were constructing the buildings in violation of the building bylaws.

news.title: Mangaluru: Sites at Konaje Layout to be allotted to public soon
news.para: The development body is currently engaged in the development of three layouts (including the one at Konaje), collectively spread across 76 acres. Of the three residential layouts, the habitat being readied at Chelyaru is the largest, sprawling across 45 acres.

news.title: Nashik civic body collects Rs 11 crore from property tax defaulters in one month
news.para: NMC has been sending teams at regular intervals to homes and commercial establishments of big defaulters to collect pending property tax dues.
